<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
If the merchants are aggressive to me, then that alone is a bug itself.  If some merchant is going to get uppity, then I'm certainly going to charm him and send him to die to the nearby Monastary.  While it is not how it *should* be according to the rules now, then either the rules or the merchants should be changed.  If people can kill them, it is the same result as if we charmed them, that being that the merchants are removed for people to use later on.<P>There are a lot of things that "should" be right now, but a lot of them, in common sense, really should not be so.  <P>-Giants should be charmable; that's just obvious, but right now, according to the rules, they "shouldn't" be.  <P>-The Amadan Touched creatures in Emain, definately zombies, but we can charm them.  They "should not" be, but take those away and you just decrease the Frontier pets even more.  <P>-The Boogy-like creatures in Emain cannot be charmed, but since they look just like our Boogey's back home, one would think they "should" be.  But they're not.<P>-Abominable Snowmen in Odin's Gate can be charmed, but how are they any more humanoid than giants?  They are charmable, and I don't know if they "should" be or not.  They just are, and again, are one of the very few Midgard Frontier Charmable Mobs.<P>-Enemy Realm Guards should not be charmable.  And they're not.  Why again?  Are none of them humanoid?  <P>Granted, we have obligations to report these things.  But a lot of these are common sense issues that, right now, they exist in a way that, while it's as it "should" be, we know it really shouldn't be.  And certainly, if we roll over a bit, we can hope that we'll be heard.  But certain things just don't make sense, and it'd be more consistent if they did.  I don't like the idea of having to test-charm a type of mob just to see if it's humanoid.  It shouldn't be such a variable system of what's humanoid and what barely doesn't classify.<P>I don't think the Amadan Touched mobs should be charmable, as they're obviously zombies.  That, sirs, is a bug.  I don't think that the enemy Guards cannot be charmed.  That, sirs, is just plain silly.
</FONT>
