A killed merchant respawns. A charmed Merchant already exists and does not respawn until the pet dies (Unless it has recently changed). Further, toting round your own personal manservant to exchange loot for coin is really a bit unfair. Unless this was also changed, yuo and any of your friends coudl then sell to the merchant.<P><BR>Some groups at one point brought a Sorc just to charm the Fletcher merchant and have access to easy arrows for scouts.<P>Also at one point the Merchants were flagged as (Sorry, old EQ word here) Beta Neutral Faction, meaning they drew no aggro on ANYTHING until they attacked. Now this I believe was definately changed, as a charmed Merchant could walk into the middle of a gorup, aggroing none of them (even as your pet) hit one and bring ONLY it back to your group.<P>Not going to get into the giant/arwanite/humanoid argument. I have argued that oen till blue in the face. My opinion?<P>If it has 2 arms, 2 legs, and maybe a head (Bogeys and such do not!) and is capable of speech and understanding a spoken language, it should do what the hell I tell it to.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
